OL,3,CChild 'unnecessarily restrained' after
OL,4,Ctrust failed to monitor use of seating
OL,6,FHarry Shakespeare was diagnosed with
OL,7,Fautism when he was three years old and
OL,8,Fis non-verbal. When he started school,
OL,9,Fhis parents noticed a change in his
OL,10,Fbehaviour.
OL,12,FEventually, Deirdre and Rodney
OL,13,FShakespeare found out their son was
OL,14,Fbeing restrained in a chair without
OL,15,Fthem knowing.
