OL,3,CChild 'unnecessarily restrained' after
OL,4,Ctrust failed to monitor use of seating
OL,6,FNow, a report by the Northern Ireland
OL,7,FPublic Services Ombudsman has said
OL,8,FHarry was "restrained unnecessarily",
OL,9,Fcriticising the Western Trust for
OL,10,Ffailing to properly monitor a school's
OL,11,Fuse of specialist seating.
OL,13,FDeirdre, Harry's Mum, said: "His
OL,14,Fpersonality had changed and he started
OL,15,Fto have panic attacks and night
OL,16,Fterrors at home so he would scream and
OL,17,Fcry.
