OL,6,FRodney, Harry's Dad, said: "You felt
OL,7,Fuseless as a father because you
OL,8,Fweren't there to be able to protect
OL,9,Fhim, but he needed protected."
OL,11,FFollowing a complaint about Harry's
OL,12,Ftreatment, the Public Services
OL,13,FOmbudsman said he was being restrained
OL,14,F"unnecessarily".
OL,16,FThe Ombudsman criticised the Western
OL,17,FTrust for failing to properly monitor
OL,18,Fa school's use of specialist seating.
