OL,4,Ctrust failed to monitor use of seating
OL,6,FThe report said when the school
OL,7,Fclaimed it was having difficulty
OL,8,Fmoving him to the dining room and
OL,9,Fasked the trust to add a wheeled base
OL,10,Fto the chair, the ombudsman concluded
OL,11,Fthat in improving and fitting the base
OL,12,Fto the chair, the trust did not fully
OL,13,Fconsider the child's human rights.
OL,15,FDeputy Ombudsman Sean Martin said:
OL,16,F"There is a need for clear guidelines
OL,17,Ffor both health and education to
OL,18,Fensure that restraint is only used
OL,19,Fwhen it's absolutely necessary.
